[b]TVO - Big Ideas, January 10, 2009: Margaret Atwood's 2008 Massey Lecture, &quot;Payback: Debt and the Shadow Side of Wealth&quot;[/b]

Preeminent author, Margaret Atwood, delivers the 2008 Massey Lecture, &quot;Payback: Debt and the Shadow Side of Wealth&quot;. Always surprising and wickedly entertaining, Atwood takes us on a highly imaginative journey, with Scrooge as her central character, to illustrate what she refers to as &quot;the debtor/creditor twinship in the broadest sense.&quot; Atwood continues, &quot;What we owe and how we pay is a feature of all human societies and profoundly shapes our shared values and our cultures&quot;.

